          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Interface">Rim</text><text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">:</text><text style="font-style:italic;">&#32;</text><text style="font-style:normal;">term for the </text>curved <text style="font-style:italic;">lines</text> that join all of the XYZ Points along the 2xFlanks, Floor, and Top of <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">3D-Cams</text>. Each Rim joins the points that you specify as the <text styleclass="Parameter-Popup">Number-of-Points</text> parameter in the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">3D-Cam dialog.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text style="font-style:italic;">Total Rims = &#160;(2 × Flank Rim Count) + (2 × Top or Root Rim Count)</text></para>
